OL,3,CAdolescence makes history at Baftas
OL,4,Cwith four wins
OL,6,FThe leading actress Bafta was won by
OL,7,FNarges Rashidi for her portrayal of
OL,8,FNazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe in Prisoner
OL,9,F951.
OL,11,FDedicating the prize to the British-
OL,12,FIranian woman who was imprisoned in
OL,13,FTehran, and her family, Rashidi said:
OL,14,F"Your resilience, your dignity, your
OL,15,Flove through impossible circumstances
OL,16,Fhave moved us all.
OL,18,F"Your courage will stay with me for
OL,19,Fthe rest of my life. This is for you."
OL,26,@vD@AOUzD@AOU{D@fO]
